07:07.798 --> 07:10.322
If you, I talked about this Wednesday night in Bible study,

07:10.946 --> 07:15.933
We read the Bible the way we see it in our text of chapter and verse.

07:16.694 --> 07:18.917
Well, the Bible was not originally written in chapter and verse.

07:18.937 --> 07:23.804
The Bible was originally, it was just, it was a scroll.

07:23.904 --> 07:26.368
It was one continuous writing.

07:26.588 --> 07:30.734
And so the concept of chapters and verses didn't come about until later in the medieval period.

07:31.875 --> 07:39.346
So what we see in John 17 is a continuation of what started in John 13.

07:39.906 --> 07:49.717
So John 13, all the way through John 17, really should be understood in one movement, one movement.

07:49.737 --> 07:51.319
