08:16.443 --> 08:25.114
And one of the primary prayers, he prays his unity, both for the disciples on the earth in that moment, but also for those of us, as he says, who would come to believe because of their testimony.

08:25.334 --> 08:27.497
So for us, he prays for unity, and that's a big deal.

08:27.838 --> 08:31.382
But this is a beautiful prayer where Jesus is praying for us as the church.

08:31.903 --> 08:35.387
And so you want to know what Jesus is praying for?

08:36.349 --> 08:37.330
He tells us.

08:38.786 --> 08:50.424
And he tells us to me what I think is so powerful and so important for us to drill down into our heads.

08:52.848 --> 08:54.190
He says, they may know eternal life.

